{"title_page": "Charles Morerod", "text_new": "{{Infobox Christian leader\n| type             = Bishop\n| honorific-prefix = His Excellency\n| name             = Charles Morerod\n| honorific-suffix = \n| native_name      = \n| native_name_lang = \n| title            = Bishop of Lausanne, Geneva and Fribourg\n| image            = Monseigneur Charles Morerod.JPG\n| image_size       = 200px\n| alt              = \n| caption          = \n| church           = [[Roman Catholic]]\n| archdiocese      = \n| province         = \n| metropolis       = \n| diocese          = [[Diocese of Lausanne, Geneva and Fribourg]]\n| see              = \n| elected          = \n| appointed        = 3 November 2011\n| term             = \n| term_start       = 11 December 2011\n| quashed          = \n| term_end         = \n| predecessor      = [[Bernard Genoud]]\n| opposed          = \n| successor        = \n| other_post       = \n<!---------- Orders\nThe Orders section may be omitted in favour of Template:Ordination for those\nclergy claiming Apostolic succession, such as Catholics, Orthodox and Anglicans. ---------->\n| ordination       = 30 April 1988\n| ordained_by      = \n| consecration     = 11 December 2011\n| consecrated_by   = [[Georges Cottier|Cardinal Georges Cottier]]\n| cardinal         = \n| created_cardinal_by =\n| rank             = \n<!---------- Personal details ---------->\n| birth_name       = \n| birth_date       = 28 October 1961\n| birth_place      = [[Riaz]], [[Switzerland]]\n| death_date       = <!-- {{Death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} (death date then birth date) -->\n| death_place      = \n| buried           = \n| nationality      = [[Swiss]]\n| religion         = \n| residence        = \n| parents          = \n| spouse           = <!-- or | partner = -->\n| children         = \n| occupation       = \n| profession       = \n| previous_post    = \n| education        =\n| alma_mater       = \n| motto            = Mihi vivere Christus est (latin) Pour moi, vivre, c\u2019est le Christ (French)\n| signature        =  \n| signature_alt    = \n| coat_of_arms     = Coat of arms of Charles Morerod.svg\n| coat_of_arms_alt = 100px\n<!---------- Sainthood ---------->\n| feast_day        = \n| venerated        = \n| saint_title      = \n| beatified_date   = \n| beatified_place  = \n| beatified_by     = \n| canonized_date   = \n| canonized_place  = \n| canonized_by     = \n| attributes       = \n| patronage        = \n| shrine           = \n| suppressed_date  = \n<!---------- Other ---------->\n| other            = \n}}\n{{Infobox bishopstyles |\n    name=Charles Morerod OP|\n    dipstyle=[[The Most Reverend]] |\n    offstyle=[[Your Excellency]] |\n    relstyle=[[Bishop]] |\n    deathstyle=not applicable |\n    image = Coat of arms of Charles Morerod.svg |\n    image_size = 200px |}}\n'''Charles Morerod''', O.P. (born 28 October 1961), is a [[Swiss (people)|Swiss]] [[Dominican Order|Dominican]] prelate. Since 2011, he has been [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Lausanne, Geneva and Fribourg|bishop of Lausanne, Geneva and Fribourg]]. Previously, he served as Rector of the [[Pontifical University of St. Thomas Aquinas]] (the Angelicum), professor of dogmatic theology,<ref name=\"pust\">{{Cite web|title=P. Prof. Dr. Charles Morerod OP |work=Facultas Philosophorum |publisher=Pontificia Universitas Studiorum a Sancto Thoma Aquinate in Urbe |date=24 August 2010 |url=http://pustphilo.org/prof/morerod/index.php |accessdate=4 January 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110727191440/http://pustphilo.org/prof/morerod/index.php |archivedate=27 July 2011 }}</ref> and Secretary General of the [[International Theological Commission]].\n\n==Biography==\nMorerod was born on 28 October 1961 in [[Riaz]], [[Switzerland]].<ref name=\"bio\">{{Cite web | title = Curriculum vit\u00e6 in English | work = Prof. Charles Morerod | publisher = Pontificia Universitas Studiorum a Sancto Thoma Aquinate in Urbe | date = 19 July 2009 | url = http://pustphilo.org/prof/morerod/curren.php | accessdate = 4 January 2011 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20110727191721/http://pustphilo.org/prof/morerod/curren.php | archive-date = 2011-07-27 | url-status = dead }}</ref> He entered the Dominican [[novitiate]] in 1983, and was [[ordination|ordained]] a priest in 1988.\n\n==Formation==\nMorerod earned a [[Licentiate (degree)|licentiate]] in theology from the [[University of Fribourg]] in 1987, and a [[doctorate]] in theology from the same university in 1994. He was [[chaplain]] to the university from 1991 to 1994. In 1996, he obtained a [[Licentiate (degree)|licentiate]] in philosophy, also from the University of Fribourg, and a doctorate in philosophy from the [[Catholic University of Toulouse]] in 2004.<ref name=\"bio\"/>\n\n==Career==\nFrom 1987 to 1989 Morerod was engaged in pastoral ministry, first as a deacon and then as vice-parish priest at the parish of St. Paul in Geneva. From 1989 to 1992 he was Assistant at the Faculty of Theology, University of Fribourg from 1991 to 1994 and chaplain of the University of Fribourg. In 1993 he received his doctorate in theology and a licentiate in philosophy in 1996. From 1994 to 1999 he was adjunct professor of Fundamental Theology at the University of Fribourg and since 1996 professor at the Pontifical University of St. Thomas Aquinas. Since 1997 he is editor of the edition in the French journal ''Nova et Vetera''. In 1999 he became full-time professor at the Pontifical University of St. Thomas Aquinas. From 1999 to 2002 he also taught at the Faculty of Theology of Lugano.  He was Vice-Dean of the Faculty of Theology from 2003 to 2009 and Dean of the Faculty of Philosophy at the Pontifical University of St. Thomas Aquinas.<ref>[http://press.catholica.va/news_services/bulletin/news/28307.php?index=28307&lang=en NOMINA DEL VESCOVO DI LAUSANNE, GEN\u00c8VE ET FRIBOURG (SVIZZERA)] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120403123942/http://press.catholica.va/news_services/bulletin/news/28307.php?index=28307&lang=en |date=April 3, 2012 }}</ref> In 2004 he obtained his doctorate in philosophy at the Catholic Institute of Toulouse. From 2008-2011, he was also academic director of the Rome program for Catholic Studies students at the University of St. Thomas in St. Paul, MN.\n\nIn April 2009 he was appointed Secretary General of the International Theological Commission and Consultant of the Congregation for the Doctrine of the Faith. Morerod was appointed rector of the Angelicum in September 2009.<ref name=\"pust\"/> He has been secretary general of the [[International Theological Commission]] since 22 April 2009,<ref>{{Cite video | title = Charles Morerod, new secretary of the International Theological Commission | publisher = Rome Reports, via YouTube | location = Rome | url = https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=xyLXb0ZWaSE | date = 9 July 2009 | accessdate = 29 June 2010}}</ref> and consultor of the [[Congregation for the Doctrine of the Faith]]. A disciple of [[Charles Journet|Charles Cardinal Journet]], he has written several theological articles in the review ''[[Nova et Vetera]]'', reflecting on the doctrinal and philosophical aspects of [[ecumenism]]. He is also an ordinary member of the [[Pontifical Academy of St. Thomas Aquinas]].\n\nSince 26 October 2009, Morerod has been a member of the team responsible for the [[dialogue between the Society of St. Pius X and the Holy See|dialogue with the Society of St. Pius X]].\n\nOn 3 November 2011 Pope Benedict XVI named Morerod Bishop of Lausanne, Geneva and Fribourg. He was consecrated on 11 December at the [[Fribourg Cathedral|Cathedral of St. Nicholas]] in Fribourg.  [[Georges Cottier|Georges Cardinal Cottier]], a fellow Dominican, was the principal consecrator.\n\nOn 12 June 2012 Bishop Morerod was appointed a member of the [[Congregation for Catholic Education]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://press.catholica.va/news_services/bulletin/news/29334.php?index=29334&lang=en |title=Archived copy |access-date=2012-06-12 |archive-url=https://archive.today/20121205091236/http://press.catholica.va/news_services/bulletin/news/29334.php?index=29334&lang=en |archive-date=2012-12-05 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\nHe was appointed a member of the [[Congregation for Divine Worship and the Discipline of the Sacraments]].<ref>[http://press.vatican.va/content/salastampa/it/bollettino/pubblico/2016/10/28/0775/01733.html]</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20161105060409/http://www.pustphilo.com/prof/morerod/index.php Faculty page at the Angelicum]\n** [https://archive.today/20140211133119/http://pustphilo.com/prof/morerod/curren.php ''Curriculum vitae'' of Fr. Morerod]\n* {{Helveticat}}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-rel|ca}}\n\n{{s-bef|before=[[Luis Ladaria Ferrer]]}} \n{{s-ttl|title=[[International Theological Commission|General Secretary of the International Theological Commission]]|years=22 April 2009 \u2013 3 November 2011}} \n{{s-aft|after=[[Serge-Thomas Bonino]]}}\n\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Morerod, Charles}}\n[[Category:1961 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from the canton of Fribourg]]\n[[Category:Swiss Dominicans]]\n[[Category:Swiss Roman Catholic theologians]]\n[[Category:International Theological Commission]]\n[[Category:Roman Catholic bishops in Switzerland]]\n[[Category:Members of the Congregation for Catholic Education]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox Christian leader\n| type             = Bishop\n| honorific-prefix = His Excellency\n| name             = Charles Morerod\n| honorific-suffix = \n| native_name      = \n| native_name_lang = \n| title            = Bishop of Lausanne, Geneva and Fribourg\n| image            = Monseigneur Charles Morerod.JPG\n| image_size       = 200px\n| alt              = \n| caption          = \n| church           = [[Roman Catholic]]\n| archdiocese      = \n| province         = \n| metropolis       = \n| diocese       